Can’t believe it’s my first time trying @baobaoshengjian 🥟 one of the FEW spots in #YEG that specializes in soup dumplings (xlb) and Chinese baos of sorts.

The real good stuff isn’t actually the XLB though. You must get the traditional pan fried baos — they are lil baos filled with piping hot pork bone soup then pan fried. Literally. Piping. Hot. 🥲

Here’s what I ordered:
🥟 XLB (6 pcs, $9.99) — the skin is a lil thick for my liking and there wasn’t enough soup but good for the price
🥒 cucumber salad ($5.69) — a refreshing palate cleanser. you can bring it home and add more cucumbers to it LOL.
🌶️ chili oil wonton ($9.29) — pretty good snacc, not really spicy tho 
🍗 crispy chicken bao ($7.99) — chicken was crispy and juicy, but I wasn’t a fan of the sweet chili sauce and the bun was dry lol

This place hit the spot when I was stuck finding a casual spot to eat! Worth it for the pricing and everything.

PS: sweatshirt is from @shop.neutralstudio, a local retailer that just started up their biz. The sweatshirts are minimalistic, comfy af, and unisex! ☺️

Meet Allen! 👋 The ramen boi behind @kaseyramen that started off as a home biz and is now selling out 200+ ramen kits every week. + He’s hosting ramen pop ups every now and then. 🍜

This is easily one of my favourite ramen to get in #YEG (if not, my favourite)! They drop new ramen kits every Wednesday with pickups in the around town on Sundays. The kits range from classic favourites to new experiments, and you can trust it to be a hit every time. Broths are bold and packed with rich umami flavour, then served with chewy noodles, char siu, and a soft boiled egg. Sometimes I like to add my own roasted seaweed too. 😎

My personal favourite: black garlic tonkotsu ✨

✨ NEW IN #YEG ✨

& yes, I’m alive still 😂. My all time favourite Japanese-style cheesecake spot has finally opened up their first location in town! Originated from #YVR, @castellacheesecake offers an array of light Japanese desserts, including cheesecake tarts, basque cheesecake, cheesecake stuffed croissants, and much more. I used to always make a pit stop here and would smuggle it on the plane back home LOL. 

I had the pleasure of visiting a day before it’s opened to the public and tried their cheesecake croissant + tiramisu for the first time. The croissant was delicious. Crispy, flakey, and creamy. Even though it’s in a small kiosk, the cheesecake was just as good as I remembered (if not better cuz it was fresh)! It’s ooey, gooey, and andddd hear me out… NOT TOO SWEET 🥹 which is the highest compliment I can give to desserts.

They’re scheduled to grand open either tomorrow or Saturday, depending on how tomorrow goes. Check their IG for updates! 🍰

One of my favourite spots when I’m craving something hearty and savoury, that’s not a soup! @filistix.dt goes hard when you want a delicious rice bowl. I used to order here a lot more frequently when I worked DT, and kinda forgot about it till now again.

This time, I tried their tapsilog and pancit for the first time. The tapsilog was an incredible combination of sweet, savoury, and salty, I literally inhaled it all at one go. They have a different weekend brunch menu and daily lunch menu. Highly recommend giving their brunch menu a try! 🇵🇭

IT’S BACKKKK 🍦

The most popular DUNKAROO ICE CREAM is back at @kindicecream for a limited time (till end of the month)! After I saw their IG, I KNEW I had to plan my trip there asap. Grabbed myself a pint + a scoop of the ice cream, and I still don’t think it was enough lol.

Their 90’s flavours are here — dunkaroo, deep n delicious, + cherry coke sorbet. I had a lil bit of my friend’s deep n delicious and it was v chocolatey, exactly like the deep n delicious.

There’s LOTS in stock so grab it while you still can! This is prob my one of my fave ice cream flavours and I think about it every month or so. 🥹

Everyone’s favourite restaurant after a day of gambling at @starlightyeg has finally reopened — Congrats @atlassteakandfish inside @official_wem! 🎉

The atmosphere is honestly perfect if you’re looking to impress a guest, trying to rizz up your date, or just want a nice spot after shopping the mall. They also have live piano every Friday and they truly excel in their hospitality. 

I tried a variety of their dishes:
• tableside chilled seafood salad
• angus beef New York striploin 
• seafood mixed grill 
• grilled Atlantic lobster tail + blue cheese gnocchi sides
• strawberry rhubarb pavlova + cheesecake

Though I enjoyed my time, I think they’re mainly good for the experience. The food itself was okay. Some were better than others and some were lacking in different areas. Maybe it was because I came on the night they literally just opened though lol.

✨ NEW IN #YEG ✨

Technically not too new cause I saw this awhile back, but didn’t get it cause it was too $$$. I had a mad craving for @thekegsteakhouse and I caved in. Did you know, they sell their billy miner pies in ice cream form?? So it’s the ice cream part of the cake with the almonds, chunks of cookie crumble crust, chocolate syrup, and caramel syrup… all mixed into a tub of ice cream. Sold conveniently at @realcanadiansuperstore. 😱 I was CONVINCED. 👏

…It was bland lol.

I finally checked out the new Northside hidden gem @gintaro_kitchen22 ! They specialize in fusion Japanese eats and classic favourites like katsu, teppanyaki, tataki, nigiri sushi, sashimi (of course), and much more. 🍣

I tried a variety of dishes: assorted sashimi, nigiri sushi, shrimp tempura, some rolls, cream udon, sunomono (cold rice noodles), and tuna tataki. 

The assorted sashimi and nigiri were easily my favourites! It was thicc and v fresh. Pricing is reasonable imo (I literally can’t wait to go Japan though) and it’s probably one of the better options for Japanese food in the Northside. 😉

Oh, I also heard their bento boxes were 👌!

Confession: I’ve been gatekeeping the Korean street foods at @hmartofficial for awhile now, but I think it’s time to share. 🤣  My favourite weekend activity had been getting a good workout in the AM, then go to H-Mart for groceries + food! 

Besides the bomb fried chicken from BBQ Chicken inside the food court, H-Mart also sells a bunch of freshly fried eats. Sometimes, if you catch them on a good day, it’d be fully stocked with new items.

The ones shown on the video are my personal faves. Some of them tends to get pricy ($6-$10 each) so make sure to look at the prices or ask them before ordering.

Definitely a treat. Definitely worth it. 

Ps. The Korean corn dogs here are also ranked pretty high up for me. 😉

✨ NEW AT COSTCO ✨

I saw these babies on TikTok a few weeks ago and I can’t believe I found them in Costco here! If you’re a big fan of Korean corn dogs, these are for you. 

They are frozen crispy potato corn dogs, individually wrapped, and sold at a pack of 8 for $16. Pricing wise, it’s a steal — $2 per corn dog. 

Taste wise… it’s also very good! Pop it in the air fryer at 400 for 12 mins (depends how crispy you like it + how strong your air fryer is), and you’re golden. 😉

It only had mozzarella cheese inside. Sometimes that’s all you need to get the cravings satisfied lol. It’s not as good as @chungchun.ca or @hmartofficial, but it’s still super convenient and at only $2 each, I have no complaints. 😌🍢

PSA 🗣️ @karensdinerofficial is on tour and had a pop up in #YEG this weekend. And here’s how it went…

Karen’s Diner is based in Australia, and has over 14 locations across Australia, UK, & USA. Clearly, poor service is appreciated to some degree. 😂 The restaurant deliberately offers an unpleasant dining experience, and the staff are meant to insult customers throughout their entire meal.

Now, I’ve seen some videos of this restaurant and thought I was prepared for it. Let me tell ya… this was something else LOL.

On top of bad service, there are interactive games involved like lap dances, karaoke at table tops, spin the wheel and dance, and so much more. My social anxiety was quaking, but this would be fun event for all you extroverts! It’s an experience for sure. Thank the Karens for not drafting me up there.🧎‍♀️

Food is by @thecanadianbrewhouse. Each ticket provides a burger, fries, and soft drink. Their next pop up returns June 24 & 25. Would you try it?!

NEW BRUNCH MENU 🍳 

@blackpearlyeg is launching their brunch menu this weekend, exclusively at their Windermere location. Just in time for Mother’s Day. 👀🌸

The menu has both seafood options and non-seafood options. They’re still finalizing a couple of things so I’m not going to get too fixated on each dish and their ingredient breakdown, but these two were my highlights: 

🦀 captains egg benny — seared haddock topped w/ king crab + caviar 
🦪 cold seafood tower — Alaskan king crab, caviar, tuna crudo, ceviche, jumbo black tiger prawns, crab legs, and oysters

For drinks, I really liked the prosecco sorbet! 🍧

There were a few minor kinks here and there. Nothing major. Feedback had been provided. Brunch will be available regularly on weekends, starting this weekend!

✨ NEW IN #YEG ✨

& my first time trying momos!! 🥹 these are plump lil spiced dumplings filled with either meat or veggies. Usually served either steamed, pan fried, or deep fried. I’ve been meaning to try them for so long now, and finally had the chance to check out this new spot in the Northside with @yegbesteats & @mshangryfoodie.

Since it’s my first time trying momos, I didn’t really have anything to compare them to besides Chinese dumplings. 😅 the momos pretty light and the flavours kinda fell off short for us. We asked for different stuffings, but I think it all came out as chicken lol. Out of all of them, the chili momo was the crowd favorite! 🥟

Maybe I’ll continue my hunt for momos elsewhere… I also wished there were more flavour in the chai tea + selroti and chana too.

✨ NEW IN #YEG ✨

@tastyhousenoodle has taken over the old @presoteaab UofA location. Their extensive menu features Chinese noodle soups, rice bowls, various snacks including some dim sum items, ramen, and much more. You know it’s real when the menu is long long. 😅

Here’s what I ordered for food:
🍜 braised beef pulled noodle — $18
🍲 sour & spicy noodle w/ beef — $16
🍗 crispy popcorn chicken — $10
🐤 salted egg yolk wings — $10

Overall, portions were generous on the noodle soups. We preferred the braised noodle soup over the spicy & sour. Popcorn chicken was dry. Salted egg yolk wings were good though — I’d go back for this! Service was also super friendly. 

🧋THE BUBBLE TEA:

They also share a space with @truebosscanada, a Taiwanese bubble tea chain and the first to introduce fruit vinegar drinks/enzyme drinks. 

What is an “enzyme” drink? 
Don’t worry, I didn’t know either and thought it was a poor translation error LOL. It’s essentially fermented fruits & vegetables that are packed with nutrients. It can help improve digestion, boost immunity, and increase metabolism. I had the fruit enzyme vinegar with plum and mango + aloe for toppings. Tbh, it wasn’t bad, but it didn’t hit. If I’m craving bbt, I’d just go for the real thing.

I finally finally (finally) tried @pals_yeg ! Yes, it’s been opened for years and and yes, it’s still my first time trying it. Something about a $19 sandwich and a long waitlist always deterred me from it. This is probably my 4th attempt to try it, and I guess 4th time was the charm lol. 

If you’re in the mood for a hearty sandwich, this spot is your PAL (😏). It’s filling, savoury, and the crust of that meatball sub cuts all the right parts on top of my mouth.

🥖 meatball sub — $19
🥪 reuben — $19

Out of the two, I really enjoyed the Reuben because it’s slightly more unique. The combination of the rye bread, pastrami, sauerkraut, swiss, and dressing were ✨🤌✨

📍 TOKYO, JAPAN

If you’re planning your trip to Japan, chances are you’ve heard of the Tsukiji Fish Market (the outer market). It’s probably the most hyped market in Japan — known to have fresh sashimi at the lowest price, various food stalls, home goods, desserts, and much more.

Here’s everything I tried. 👆

It’s pretty touristy and wasn’t really for me, but it could be for you! 

Try to get there a little before 9 am so you’re first in line at the stalls. My favourite was the fresh otoro (5 pieces for $10) 😍 You just pick it out, pull over to the side, rip open the container, and eat. & Make sure to bring cash with you cause a lot of vendors still don’t take card.

You’ve had chicken and waffles for brunch before, but have you had it together in an ice cream format?! 😱 @madebymarcus launched their July flavours and this month, there’s a chicken and waffles mixed in with real waffles. 🧇

Don’t worry, there’s isn’t any real chicken pieces 😂 it’s chicken boullion. It tastes like similar to their sea salt & goat milk flavour with waffles, imo!

IT’S BACKKKK 🍑 

The TikTok famous peach shaped ice creams are back at @tt_supermarket for $8.28 per box (3 inside). They’ve been here for over a month already so if you’re looking to stock up anytime soon, here’s your chance!

Note: the peach flavour is pretty light and doesn’t taste like artificial peach, which I actually prefer! 

Psst… word on the streets is that there’s a MANGO version of this ice cream. If you ever see those around, you know who to call. 👀

📍T&T Northgate — I also saw them at the WEM location last month!

[TOKYO, JAPAN] 🇯🇵

Omakase is an absolute mussttt if you’re in Japan. This was my 2nd omakase while I was there, and I’m so glad I got to sneak one more in before I left. There’s 3 locations available — Marunouchi, Nihonbashi, & Hibiya. I went to the Nihonbashi location. 

✨ JAPAN TIP: you haveeee to book resos at least the morning of or a day in advance to get into any highly rated spots. + most places take online resos! 

Pros: affordable, 20+ courses, delicious.
Cons: sushi chef isn’t as personable as other omakases.

Overall: highly recommend + currently having major post-Asia withdrawals. 😭

There’s a new small batched ice cream shop in #YEG, and it’s currently all the hype right now!🍦

@whiterabbit_icecream started off as a food truck, and now has opened up their storefront location near MacEwan! It’s actually my first time trying their products… ever. The service was so friendly and even offered to let us sample all their flavours 🥹 — we only tried like 3 cuz we felt bad though LOL. I ended up getting a split single scoop of white rabbit milk tea + cereal milk.

I wished the white rabbit milk tea had a stronger flavour, but I still really liked it. The cereal milk was perfect though. + all the flavours are ✨not too sweet✨

This might be my next addiction for the rest of summer… 🤣

FILIPINO ISKRAMBOL (aka ice scramble) 🍧

When I was grabbing ice cream on the weekend, I stumbled into a new bubble tea spot called @thebigsquishdowntown 🧋This is their second location in #YEG with the first being in Bonnie Doon. They’re Filipino owned, specializing in your standard bubble teas while offering unique lemonades, ice scrambles, halo halo, bubble waffles, waffle sticks, and more! 

Ice scramble is a frozen dessert made from banana-flavoured shaved ice mixed with evaporated milk and sugar, then topped with powdered milk, marshmallows, and chocolate syrup. I got mine with tapioca pearls too for an extra $0.50. You can’t adjust the sugar/sweetness level here.

The portions were generous for $8. Now, I really really wanted to like it, but it just wasn’t for me. It was VERY artificially sweet and I ended up throwing it out after 3-4 sips/bites lol 🥲

Maybe I’ll try their halo halo next time!

✨ NEW IN #YEG ✨

The next time you’re craving a flakey Jamaican patty, check out the newest spot in town — @lloydspattydistro that specializes solely on Jamaican patties (with more menu items to come 👀)

They currently offer 3 flavours: beef, chicken, & vegetarian. Spicy or regular. Cheese optional. Coco bread option. My favourite was the spicy beef with coco bread! & Personally, I liked it better without the cheese so all the flavours can shine through. 

📸: single patty — $4.80 
🧀: with cheese — $5.05
🍞: coco bread — $2.50

Orrr, you can also buy a box of 10, fresh or frozen, for $35-38!

Looking for your next Sunday brunch spot?🍴

Recently I visited @l1l2yeg inside WEM for their Sunday brunch buffet. It’s available every Sunday from 10:30 am to 2:30 pm, $49/adult & $25 kids 6-12.

There are tons of options — crab legs, mussels, shrimps, prime rib, fresh omelettes, and smoked salmon to name a few. It’s a great option if you want a variety of food!

I only got in 2 rounds before tapping out to dessert 😅 My favourite thing there was easily the fresh waffles, it was soo good and we kept going for seconds.

How much do you think you can eat?!

✨ NEW IN #YEG ✨

@kpot_yeg has taken over the old Chef Hung on Whyte Ave, and now offers Hong Kong style clay pot rice bowls starting at $18.88. Each bowl comes with their own side dish to choose from. 

I tried both the chicken fiesta (pan-fried chicken thighs) with corn + Taiwan fusion (Taiwanese sausage and tender chicken) with fried tofu. 

There’s also a “blaze” option which essentially crisps up the rice at the bottom for scorched rice — would recommend doing this too for yours! It takes an extra 20 mins.

Okay, harder review. The chicken fiesta is like your standard chicken bowl but the “blazed” crispy rice was yummy. Taiwan bowl lacks in flavour and the rice was mushy/soggy even though it was also “blazed.” Fried tofu was the best thing. Soy sauce was on the sweeter end. They’re still in early opening stages, + the service was super friendly. I’d recommend the chicken fiesta and fried tofu side if you go. 🍚🐓

Biggest congratulations @scoopnroll on the second storefront at @shopcurrents!! 🎉🙌

Now, all you lucky southsiders have another ice cream shop in the area, open all year round. Similar to their griesbach location, they have the classic rolled ice creams, soft serve, and take-home ice cream cakes. 🎂

Each cup is $8.99 and you can customize it to your liking. I think I found my new favourite — mango base with strawberry + almond topping. OR, pistachio with strawberry + nutella! 

📍5098 Windermere Blvd.

The highly anticipated and highly popular spot for fried chicken is finally opened!! 🍗🎉

After 35 years of business, Ralphs Fried Chicken was forced to close down their Srathearn location last year. Luckily, they’ve reopened their doors to the other side of town, in the Northside. Same ownership. Same old recipes. I actually didn’t try their old location before, but can confirm that the fried chicken + spud combo was a greasy delicious treat. 

💡Did you know, they have the exact same secret recipe as Sunshine Food Store?! I’ve been meaning to try Ralphs because I heard it was very similar. Can also confirm the similarities except Sunshine has the hint of nostalgia for me! 

🐓 4-piece chicken meal ($15.24) — includes spuds + slush or pop.

Hours: 11 am — 8 pm (subject to change).

TORONTO TOP 10 MUST EATS🍴

The meals that had completely blew my mind because of how good they were. 

🔖 Save this post for your next trip to #YYZ: 

1. @pizzeriabadiali — classic NY pizza. I tried a variety of different slices and they were 👌
2. @frescapizzatoronto — must get the margherita pizza w/ garlic oil 🧄
3. @burgerdrops — literally the best smash burgers I’ve ever had. Greasy but bomb af 🥹
4. @famiglia_baldassarre — 10/10 worth the lineup. You can’t go wrong with any of their daily pastas. Make sure to go early + line up!
5. @gusto101to — also another classic spot for 🍝
6. @sevenlivesto — on the pricier end for tacos but their blackened cod fish tacos were 🔥
7. @paitoronto — make sure you go to the downtown location instead of uptown (it’s better) the pork skewers, pad see ew, and pad gra prow with ground beef were my favourites
8. @416snackbar — delicious small plates. the menu seems simple yet it’s well executed. there’s a rotating menu + reg menu, just ask the server for their recos if you go ☺️

Last two that are worth mentioning:
🍨 @mizzicagelato for dessert
🍢 @kevinstaiyaki inside Pat Central for custard taiyakis

Whether you’re going to Toronto for @veldmusicfestival, or just a simple getaway, definitely check out any of those spots! Most of them are pretty casual and don’t require resos.

@boxcarcoffeeshop is the newest local coffee shop in the Northside, tucked away in the Calder neighborhood. 🏡

The space is super aesthetic and cozy. I can imagine coming here regularly for coffee catch ups or if I’m hoping to get some work done. There’s some indoor seating + a cute patio right outside. Just look for the newly renovated glass building in the area. 👀

I had their:
☕️ reg drip coffee, iced ($2.95) 
🌰 praline tart ($5.75) — I loved this tart! it has a nice nutty flavour and the texture was perfect.
🍪 rosette cookie ($2.25) — crunchy “churro cookie” with cinnamon & sugar. It’s exactly what it sounds like + more sweet. I’d pass on it next time. 

Either way, it’s definitely worth a visit and one of the few great coffee shops in the Northside!

✨ NEW BBT IN #YEG ✨

Welcome @tigersugar.jasperave! 🤗 This popular chain from Taiwan has finally opened their first
location in Edmonton. They’re known for their signature “tiger stripes” in their brown/black sugar sugar series! 🐅

| was lucky to preview the store + try a few drinks:
🧋brown sugar creme brulee milk w/ boba

[TOKYO, JAPAN] 🇯🇵 

I’m a little late with my travel content, but better late than never right… 😅 here is my top 5 must try spots in Tokyo:

🍜 @ramennagi_jp —📍Shinjuku 
I didn’t actually eat that much ramen in Japan! Especially in Tokyo. Maybe this spot hit different cause it was actually my first meal there. It’s a tiny spot tucked upstairs that’s opened 24/7. I loved how the broth was full bodied and rich. Noodles were perfectly chewy. 

🥩 @bebuya_official — 📍Shibuya 
$45/person for ayce A4 wagyu? Say lessss. Make sure to make a reso online because it gets super packed here!

I was only able to fit in 2 omakases when I was in Japan, and this one was super memorable. I opted for the $65 menu option which included 11 items. 

🥩 @gyukatsu_motomura — 📍Various
Literally melt in your mouth beef cutlets. Smol tip: there’s usually a huge line up in every spot, go on Google maps and find the least busy spot!

🍗 Lawsons — 📍Various 
Japan convenience stores are simply ✨elite✨ lol you know I had to add one in here 🥹 I pretty much had convenience store food everyday while I was there and had all the drinks, onigiri, snacks, etc! It’s Lawsons > 711 > family mart for me 😉 Make sure to get the spicy chicken cutlets for a quick 24/7 snack!

[KYOTO, JAPAN] 🇯🇵 

I was in Kyoto for 4 days and got to try a whole lot of … everything lol! A lot of $$$ spent with 2 spots that really stood out for me. 🍜

📍wajoryomen sugari 
📍tsurukame 

Both spots had literally the best tsukemen ever — the tonkotsu based broths were so flavourful and rich, and the noodles were perfectly chewy. I think I actually prefer tsukemen > ramen now cause I can have better control of my noodle texture (I’m v picky on the texture 😅). 

Both spots also get super busy! I was lucky with Tsurukame, but Wajoryomen had a lineup 30 mins before they opened.

I finally tried @diepieyeg for the first time ever! If you don’t know, they’re a FULLY VEGAN restaurant in #YEG, and the first vegan pizzeria to exist in Alberta. 

The menu consists of pastas, pizzas, chicken from @seitansyeg, and much more. I didn’t go in with too much expectations, but I actually enjoyed it here and loved the sourdough/Neapolitan-style pizzas crust. I also gave some leftovers to my carnivore friends and they also echoed that it was good too! 🍕 a nice floppy middle and chewy crust.

For pastas, we tried their lions mane gomiti, pickle Mac & cheese, and the new lazy lasagna which were all pretty good too. As a potato lover, their fries stood out the most — literally SO good and I couldn’t stop picking at them the entire time. 🤣

My recommendations: Big Mack pizza, lions mane gomiti, & truffle parm fries. AND they also make their own kombucha in house (also recommend)!!

As the title suggests, it’s a seafood restaurant! 🐟 There’s not many seafood spots in this landlocked city, so I was very happy to see another place pop up. 🎏 sea bass ($45)
